      "author": "aleksejs1",
      "description": "Big refactoring of frontmatter generation.\r\n\r\nImplement VCF naming strategy with obsidian-vcf-contacts compatibility #15\r\nMajor features:\r\n- Added VCF naming strategy with vCard-compliant field mappings (EMAIL, TEL, ADR, ORG, etc.)\r\n- Implemented [index] notation for multiple values (e.g., EMAIL[2], TEL[3])\r\n- Address fields now split into subfields for VCF strategy:\r\n  * ADR.STREET, ADR.CITY, ADR.COUNTRY, ADR.POSTALCODE, ADR.EXTENDED, ADR.TYPE\r\n  * Multiple addresses indexed: ADR[2].STREET, ADR[2].CITY, etc.\r\n- Disabled sync timestamp field for VCF strategy (better vCard compatibility)\r\n- Removed wiki link formatting [[name]] for organizations in VCF strategy\r\nOther improvements:\r\n- Restored Google ID field for Default strategy (key: 'id')\r\n- VCF strategy uses X-GOOGLE-ID for Google contact ID\r\n- Removed UID field (no longer needed)\r\n- Added suffix and index properties to ExtractionResult interface for subfield grouping\r\n- Extended KeyNamingStrategy interface to support field suffixes\r\nAll changes maintain backward compatibility with Default naming strategy.",
      "downloadCount": 4,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "1.1.0",
      "prerelease": false,
